author: Inside Edition
description: According to a joint Miami Herald / WLRN investigation (https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/article308679915.html) , the Brightline passenger train in Florida has been  linked to over 180 deaths since its launch in 2017. Brightline has not been found at fault for any of the deaths on the tracks. In a statement to INSIDE EDITION, Brightline says, although tragic, all of those fatal train strikes were preventable and "the result of illegal, deliberate behavior by people putting themselves in harm’s way."
title: Is This The 'Deadliest Train' In America?

author: Inside Edition
description: The Nobel Peace Prize was awarded to Maria Corina Machado, a woman from Venezuela fighting for democracy against a tyrannical regime, but the MAGA world is outraged. Meanwhile President Donald Trump was seen leaving the Walter Reed Medical Center Friday. Many are asking why Trump is having another medical check-up, just six months after his annual physical. In recent months, Trump's bruised right hand and swollen ankles have caused concern, but he says he feels fine.
title: Why Did President Trump Have Another Medical Check-Up?

author: Inside Edition
description: A man stole a 13-foot-tall Jack Skellington decoration. The giant outdoor figure is put up every year at a home in Corona, California. It's based on the character from the movie "The Nightmare Before Christmas." The man hauled it away and loaded it onto the roof of his car. A neighbor's security camera recorded the skeleton-napping, and she informed the unsuspecting family. Avelina Rodriguez and her husband were the proud owners of the stolen decoration. They spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Man Steals 13-Foot Jack Skellington Halloween Decoration From Home

author: Inside Edition
description: Ronald Exantus was arrested amid a national outcry over his release 10 days ago. Exantus stabbed to death 6-year-old Logan Tipton during a home invasion near Lexington, Kentucky in 2015. He claimed he had a psychotic break and could not remember the incident. He was found not guilty of murder by reason of insanity. He was sentenced to 20 years for assault. Good behavior and education credits earned him automatic early release. Cops say Exantus failed to register as a felon in central Florida.
title: Florida Police Arrest Child-Killer Ronald Exantus After Release

author: Inside Edition
description: Surveillance video captured the moment an elderly woman was attacked by a bear. It happened in a residential neighborhood in the Akita Prefecture in Japan. The 82-year-old woman was reportedly out for a morning walk when the bear attacked her in a parking lot near a railway station. Surveillance video from a nearby business recorded the incident, in which the woman can be heard yelling in horror. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 82-Year-Old Woman Attacked By Bear In Japan

author: Inside Edition
description: A family had just moved into a new house outside Seattle. They were in the garage and their 3-year-old son was playing on the front lawn when he found what he thought was a toy.
title: 3-Year-Old Brings Home Live Grenade #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: When 10-year-old Leah and her 7-year-old brother Logan started bouncing on a trampoline, a candy lodged in Logan's throat. He started choking, so Leah sprang into action.
title: Hero Sister Saves Her Little Brother's Life In Choking Scare #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Leigh Wainscott thought she had found true love when she met Jeffrey Manchester, who told her he worked for the government. In reality, Manchester had just escaped from state prison.
title: The Wild True Story Behind 'Roofman' #shorts
